<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4260] Expose a command to manually trigger an HLog roll</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4260</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4222&quot; title=&quot;Make HLog more resilient to write pipeline failures&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4222&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4222&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a version of HLog.rollWriter() that allows &quot;forcing&quot; a log roll when requested.  It would be useful to expose this as an HRegionInterface RPC method and provide a corresponding shell command to allow explicit log rolling when desired.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
